Privacy Policy and Notice at Collection
Effective Date: July 1, 2023
Below is our Privacy Policy. It is long, but worth the read as it explains how we use your personal information. At a high-level, we wanted to explain what personal information we process for Among Us and our website.
Among Us:
To protect our child users, we use your date of birth, country, and IP address to verify whether you are a child.
To create an account, we will collect your username, IP address, and email address. If you are a child user, we will send your parent’s email to Kids Web Services, so your parent can set your permissions regarding personal information for our game.
To link your account with another game platform account, we will use your username and online IDs, and in some cases, your IP address and email address.
If you buy something in-game, we may receive additional personal information to fulfill those purchases such as your name, address, and payment information.
If you are in a lobby when another user reports you for violations of our Terms of Use or other inappropriate conduct, your username, IP address, and gameplay information may be stored for moderation purposes.
If you reach out to us directly, we may use that information to help fix the problem you reported.
We do not collect any sensitive information from you, such as your precise geolocation, or sell or share your personal information for ads or profiling purposes.
Please do not put private information in your username or chat. Someone may use or save it even if we do not.
Website:
If you buy something on our website, we will use your name, postal address, telephone number, email address, payment information, and purchase history to fulfill those orders.
If you sign up for our marketing newsletter, we will use the email address you provide.
If you reach out to us directly, we may use the information provided to help fix the problem you reported.
Innersloth LLC, a Washington limited liability company (“
we
,” “
us
,” “
our
,” and their derivatives) provides websites, including
www.innersloth.com
and its subdomains (collectively, the “
Website
”), the videogame known as “Among Us” (the “
Game
”), and other online services (collectively, with the Website and the Game, the “
Services
”).
1
.
What does this Policy cover?
This Privacy Policy and Notice at Collection (this “
Policy
”) sets forth how we collect, use, protect, store, disclose, and otherwise process your Personal Information (defined below). Because we do not process any Personal Information for our videogames known as “Dig2China,” “Henry Stickmin Collection,” and “Among Us VR,” those games are not covered by this Policy. You should review Schell Games’
Privacy Policy
for more information about how it collects, uses, and shares the Personal Information it obtains and uses for “Among Us VR.”
This Policy also does NOT apply to information you provide to any third party or is collected by any third party (except as otherwise provided below).
By using our Services, you are confirming that you understand English well enough to understand this Policy. Should you have questions about this Policy, please contact us by emailing us at
privacy@innersloth.com
or mailing your questions to Innersloth LLC, PO Box 2532, Redmond, WA 98073, USA.
2. How do we process Children’s Personal Information?
A “
Child
” is a person under the age needed to consent to the processing of Personal Information in their country of residence (for example, 13 years old in the United States and between 13 and 16 years old in the European Union). Please see below for a summary of our practices with respect to the collection of Personal Information from Children and the use and disclosure of such information.
Quick-Chat Mode
If a user of our Game self-identifies or is identified by us as being a Child (each, a “
Child User
”), their gameplay experience will automatically be set to “Quick-Chat Mode,” unless the parent or legal guardian of the Child permits otherwise. Child Users in Quick-Chat Mode are restricted from communicating with or otherwise making their Personal Information publicly available to other users of our Game. Child Users will only be able to use a set of fixed phrases to communicate with other users in Quick-Chat Mode and will not have links to social media in our Game. Each of these features is designed to limit our access and the access of other users of our Game to the Personal Information of Child Users in compliance with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act of 1998 and its rules (“
COPPA
”).
Accounts
Child Users may register an account with us using a registration process similar to the one adults go through; however, in compliance with COPPA, Child Users will first be subject to a parental notice and verified parental consent process. To initiate the registration and consent process for a Child User, we collect a parent or legal guardian’s email address. We will automatically generate randomized usernames for registered Child Users, unless the parent or legal guardian grants the Child User permission to create a custom username.
Child Users using an Apple or Google family sharing account are not permitted to register another account with us and are subject to the most restrictive privacy settings in the Game.
Use and Disclosure
The Personal Information we collect from or about Child Users is used to give them access to certain features of our Game and communicate with a parent or legal guardian about the Child User’s registration, including for the purpose of verifying their information in connection with the registration. We do not share or otherwise disclose Child Users’ Personal Information, except (1) as may be necessary to protect the safety of a Child, including by disclosing their Personal Information, where appropriate, to law enforcement agencies or for an investigation related to public safety; (2) to enable us to take precautions against liability; (3) to protect the integrity, safety, and security of our Game; or (4) where required to do so by law or legal process.
We and the third-party service providers listed below may collect or maintain Child Users’ Personal Information through our Game. You should review their privacy policies linked below.
Kids Web Services
(a parental and legal guardian consent management provider);
Zendesk, Inc.
and
Keywords Studios Plc
(each a player support service provider);
ModSquad, Inc.
(a moderation service provider); and
Epic Games, Inc.
(in its capacity as a backend service provider (for example, for account management and linking)).
When a parent or legal guardian consents to permitting their Child User’s account to be linked with any of the below third party digital content stores and game platforms, we may receive such Child User’s Personal Information through our Game. You should review their privacy policies linked below.
Itch Corp.
;
Epic Games, Inc.
;
Google LLC
;
Microsoft Corp.
;
Apple Inc.
;
Valve Corp.
;
Sony Interactive Entertainment LLC
; and
Nintendo of America Inc.
Please contact us with questions about our service providers’ privacy policies and our collection and use practices by emailing us at
privacy@innersloth.com
with the subject line “Children’s Privacy” or mailing your request to Innersloth LLC, PO Box 2532, Redmond, WA 98073, USA.
At any time, a parent or legal guardian may review their Child’s Personal Information retained by us, require us to correct or delete such Personal Information, request that we delete their Child’s account, and/or refuse to permit us from further collecting or using their Child’s Personal Information by contacting us using the email or mailing address provided above. To protect parents and legal guardians’ privacy and security and the privacy and security of Child Users, we may require a parent or legal guardian to take certain steps or provide additional information, which we will keep strictly confidential, to verify their identity before we provide any information about the Child or take the requested actions.
Kids Web Services
Our Game is provided and operated by us. However, some functionalities of our Game, including the parent portal and contact with parents for purposes of obtaining verified parental consent and informing parents of their Child User’s online activities, are operated by Kids Web Services (“
KWS
”). You may contact Kids Web Services directly
here
or
privacy@kidswebservices.com
for any questions related to their use of Personal Information. KWS’s privacy policy can be found
here
.
Kids Web Services
is designed specifically to power kid-friendly registrations and digital experiences, as well as parental management tools, across the web and mobile ecosystem in compliance with the COPPA and Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 (General Data Protection Regulation). KWS is certified as COPPA-compliant by the kidSAFE Seal Program, an FTC-Approved COPPA Safe Harbor Program. The kidSAFE Seal Program is an independent safety certification service and seal-of-approval program designed exclusively for children-friendly websites and technologies, including child-targeted game sites, educational services, virtual worlds, social networks, mobile apps, connected products, and other similar interactive services and technologies. Click on the seal or go to
www.kidsafeseal.com
for more information. To learn more about COPPA, you may also consult this simple one-page informational guide from the kidSAFE Seal Program:
www.kidsafeseal.com/knowaboutcoppa.html
.
Kids Web Services is also a valid licensee, and participating member, of the Entertainment Software Rating Board’s Privacy Certified Program (“
ESRB Privacy Certified
”). To protect your privacy, Kids Web Services has voluntarily undertaken this privacy initiative, and its services have been reviewed by ESRB Privacy Certified to meet established online information collection, use, and disclosure practices. As a licensee of this privacy program, Kids Web Services’ services are subject to audits and other enforcement and accountability mechanisms administered independently by ESRB Privacy Certified.
